description: None

description: None

description: None

description: Nick Fury, captured by Hydra! Will S.H.I.E.L.D.'s fiercest agent reveal his operation's HQ? Not on your life! Fury pulls the wool over Hydra's eyes. Doctor Strange must save the woman he loves from Dormammu and his Mindless Ones.

title: Tales to Astonish  #71
description: None

description: Nothing can stop the Juggernaut, but the X-Men will go down trying! Guest-starring the Human Torch!

description: Sgt. Fury and the Howling Commandos travel the Burma Road to rescue Sister Theresa and her orphans.

title: Strange Tales  #137
description: Hydra assumes the position for a full-on nuclear launch. The target? All of Earth's nations! The clock is ticking as Fury must disable Hydra's Betatron bomb. Comrades Gabe Jones and Dum Dum Dugan assist! After probing the mind of the Ancient One, Doctor Strange gets closer to Eternity.

title: Two-Gun Kid  #78
description: None

title: Sgt. Fury  #24
description: Nick Fury's Fighting Fanatics on furlough?! Surely this cannot be!

description: Disgraced and disbanded, the troubles continue as the Avengers try to clear their good names. And for Captain America, that means a showdown with Power Man! But even if the team is found innocent, will it be enough to keep them intact?

description: An enigmatic thief known as the Cat Burglar has robbed J. Jonah Jameson, and Spider-Man is after the reward for his capture!

title: Fantastic Four  #44
description: When Johnny discovers the escaped Medusa hiding in his car, she demands he drive her out of the city! However, they can't seem to escape the evil Gorgon, who has come for Medusa!

title: Journey Into Mystery  #122
description: Thor is blackmailed by reporter Harris Hobbs, who has snagged pictures of the Thunder God transitioning from Thor to Don Blake!

title: Tales of Suspense  #71
penciler: Don Heck, George Tuska, Jack Kirby
description: Happy Hogan has been critically injured bringing a new component for Iron Man's armor to the battle field... where the Golden Avenger is battling the Titanium Man.

title: Tales to Astonish  #73
description: None

title: Uncanny X-Men  #14
description: For the first time, the Sentinels walk the Earth! To protect humanity from mutantkind, they've decided to conquer the world - and only the X-Men can stop them!

title: Sgt. Fury  #25
description: Sergeant Nick Fury is surrounded, but if we've learned one thing, never EVER count him out.

title: Avengers  #23
description: Captain America has left the Avengers! But when Kang the Conqueror abducts the remaining team and imprisons them in his future, who else can save them but the Star-Spangled Avenger?

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #31
description: The First Appearance of Gwen Stacy and Harry Osborn! Spider-Man starts college! But before he does, the web-slinger must track down some crooks who have recently acquired nuclear cargo. With Aunt May ill at home, and Peter's personal life in disarray, will Spider-Man be able to tackle freshman year and a new villain by the name of Master Planner?

title: Fantastic Four  #45
description: The First Appearance of the Inhumans!  Johnny meets a girl name Crystal and soon discovers she is Inhuman! Upon meeting her family, Johnny recognizes Medusa and immediately calls the Fantastic Four for backup. Their mysterious leader Black Bolt arrives and the two teams face off!

description: Nick Fury gets an unlikely assist from Agent G, the Imperial Hydra's daughter. The Imperial Hydra must find out where Braino-saur is, the only machine that can disrupt the Betatron bomb! In his strange tale, Doctor Strange does battle with Baron Mordo.

title: Tales of Suspense  #72
penciler: Don Heck, George Tuska, Jack Kirby
description: Returning to America following his battle against the Titanium Man, Iron Man begins to worry over the fate of his bodyguard Happy Hogan, who was critically injured in that battle.

title: Tales to Astonish  #74
description: None

title: Uncanny X-Men  #15
description: Part Two of the first X-Men vs. Sentinels storyline! The world's strangest teens have penetrated the rogue robots' citadel, but it'll be a lot harder to escape!

title: Avengers Annual  #1
description: The Mandarin is back and he's planning something big! The Avengers scramble across the globe to stop him, but can their efforts really triumph over the Mandarin's villainy? Plus, and unexpected appearance of Ultimo!

title: Daredevil  #11
description: Who is the mysterios Organizer?  And can Daredevil stop primal threats the likes of Frog-Man, Bird Man and more animal themed evil?

title: Daredevil Annual  #1
description: Daredevil's having a tough week. A flu bug has rendered his radar power useless, a Yakuza gang is trying to reclaim their power in Hell's Kitchen, and there's a murder to be solved. Now, he has to deal with a visitor from his time in prison-Carlos LaMuerto, a.k.a. the Black Tarantula. Carlos has been released, and he's looking to Matt Murdock for some help in setting up a new life on the outside. Will Murdock and LaMuerto end up as allies, or foes? Will Black Tarantula really go straight, or will his inner demons lure him back to his crime-lord past?48 PGS./Rated T  ...$3.99

title: Two-Gun Kid  #79
description: None

title: Sgt. Fury  #26
description: A U.S. crew has been captured aboard a Nazi ship! If there is any bright side however, it's that "Dum-Dum" Dugan has a plan.

title: Avengers  #24
description: The Avengers are up against insurmountable odds when Kang the Conqueror's endless army attacks. But when his own troops attempt an insurrection, Kang and the Avengers must join forces to save Princess Ravonna, Kang's unwilling bride-to-be!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #32
description: The true identity of the Master Planner revealed! But why is the villain collecting radioactive materials? And what's with those strange experiments? Plus, Peter continues to deal with the stresses of Aunt May's illness and the pressures of being a full-time student.

title: Daredevil  #12
description: The Man without Fear takes on the Plunderer, infamous pirate of the high seas! But what has brought the Plunderer aboard a cruise ship? And where is he planning on taking Matt Murdock? As Daredevil, Matt saves wild man Ka-Zar from a carnivorous plant of the Savage Land!

title: Fantastic Four  #46
description: While the Fantastic Four are fighting the Inhumans, someone called "The Seeker" arrives. They learn that The Seeker is trying to bring back those who have escaped from the Great Refuge! The Fantastic Four soon recognize another captive of The Seeker... Triton!

title: Fantastic Four Annual  #1
description: None

title: Strange Tales  #140
description: The Imperial Hydra revealed! Who is Hydra's Head of Terror, and what will he do when the Betatron bomb is activated? Agent G makes her full defection to S.H.I.E.L.D., while Tony Stark saves the day! All the lords and ladies of the mystical realm watch Doctor Strange duel with Dormammu.

title: Tales of Suspense  #73
penciler: Gene Colan, Jack Kirby, George Tuska
description: Iron Man learns that Hogan has been kidnapped from the hospital, and he follows the clues to a secret castle.

title: Tales to Astonish  #75
description: What will the Hulk do with the Watcher's Ultimate Machine?

title: Uncanny X-Men  #16
description: Have the Sentinels triumphed over the X-Men, or will they be struck down from within their own ranks? Before it's over, someone will die!

title: Sgt. Fury  #27
description: The reason behind Fury's eyepatch, revealed in this issue!

title: Tales of Suspense  #74
penciler: Gene Colan, George Tuska, Jack Kirby
description: When Iron Man is left for dead by the Black Knight, he calls upon Pepper Potts to come to his rescue.

title: Avengers  #25
description: Fooled into visiting Latveria by a spurious letter from their aunt, Quicksilver, the Scarlet Witch, and the rest of the Avengers are jailed, left at the whims of the country's iron-fisted (and faced) ruler - Doctor Doom!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #33
description: Steve Ditko buries Spidey, mirroring a scene from the book's interior--one that would go on to help define Spider-Man for all time.

title: Daredevil  #13
description: Stranded and unconscious in the Savage Land, Daredevil finds himself at the mercy of Maa-Gor, brutal leader to the Man-Apes. Will Daredevil be able to stave off this threat despite his lack of powers? Plus, the mysterious origin of Ka-Zar is revealed by Plunderer, and Karen Page worries over Matt's disappearance.

title: Fantastic Four  #47
description: The Fantastic Four meet up with Black Bolt in this issue and have discovered a way to track down the Inhumans!

title: Strange Tales  #141
description: S.H.I.E.L.D.'s battle with Hydra comes to a head, leading to the death of a key player. Plus, what is Operation Brain Blast? S.H.I.E.L.D. delves into the realm of the supernatural with a new ESP division. Will Fury become the first unwilling subject? Doctor Strange reaches an agreement with Dormammu. Clea is banished to a much darker dimension.

title: Tales to Astonish  #76
description: The Hulk finds himself in a dystopian future, attacked by an army of King Arrkam's warriors!

title: Uncanny X-Men  #17
description: The first Sentinel Saga is over, but metal can be dangerous even when it's not in the form of robots! Just ask...Magneto!

inker: Mike Esposito as Mickey Demeo, Mike Esposito
description: None

description: Check out Stan Lee's final issue on "Sgt. Fury"! For the first time, we see a Nazi display remorse…

title: Avengers  #26
description: The Wasp is captured by Attuma, who threatens to flood the world with his Wave Machine! It's up to the Avengers to stop him, of course!

penciler: Dick Ayers, Jack Kirby, Gene Colan
description: When using the Enervation Intensifier device in order to heal Happy Hogan of his wounds, Iron Man accidentally transforms his friend and body guard into a horrible creature dubbed "The Freak".

title: Uncanny X-Men  #18
description: Magneto sends the X-Men on a balloon ride of death! Only Iceman remains to challenge him!

title: Fantastic Four  #48
description: The First Appearance of Silver Surfer and Galactus!  Introducing the World-Eater and his enigmatic herald, the Silver Surfer, as the Fantastic Four stand in defense of Earth in one of the most beloved sagas ever told!

title: Strange Tales  #142
description: Mentallo and Fixer combine their power for one dangerous attack. S.H.I.E.L.D. can't sense them coming, and Fury is taken unawares. This is one time the good guys can't win! Strange drops into his astral form, getting the drop on Demonicus.

title: Tales to Astonish  #77
description: None

title: Sgt. Fury  #29
description: Baron Strucker begins a dangerous new occupation, and an entire French town is at the disposal of his rage!

title: Tales of Suspense  #76
description: While being arrested for the use of the Enervation Intensifier, Tony Stark is suddenly transported through time and space. But where will he end up?

title: Avengers  #27
description: The Avengers' showdown with Attuma comes to a head! But why did the Beetle infiltrate Avengers Mansion to keep Hawkeye from reading a secret message? And what does it all have to do with the Wasp?

description: He's got all of the X-Men's powers but none of their sanity: the Mimic! He's out to join the team or destroy it, and he doesn't really care which!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #35
description: Who is the Molten Man? And what forces can take down a villain with near-impenetrable skin? Plus, Peter tries to earn some fast cash from his freelance photography, only to find that the Bugle has undergone some recent changes.

description: The Hulk is back in the present, but his secret is out...Bruce Banner is the Hulk!

title: Sgt. Fury  #30
description: Surrounded by a ferocious Italian troop, Sergeant Fury has to decide…surrender or die?

title: Tales of Suspense  #77
penciler: Gene Colan, Jack Kirby, John Romita Sr.
description: The first appearance of Peggy Carter!  Captain America joins forces with a French Resistance group led by a woman who he would come to know as Peggy Carter.  Plus, the Mandarin and his prisoner Tony Stark converse in his castle about the Mandarin’s construction of the giant android called Ultimo.

title: Avengers  #28
description: Goliath joins the Avengers, and just in time - the Wasp has been captured by the Beetle and the Collector!

title: Uncanny X-Men  #20
description: It's mutant mania when the Blob and Unus tag-team the X-Men! Featuring the origin of Professor X!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #36
description: Scientist Norton Fester is studying a meteor that has recently crashed near New York. But when the meteor unleashes radioactive energy, Fester is transformed into supper-baddie, the Looter! Spider-Man is in college and in trouble. The Looter's irradiated super-strength may prove to be Spidey's toughest battle yet!

title: Fantastic Four  #50
description: Behold…Galactus concludes!  The Silver Surfer takes on Galactus in an epic battle! Meanwhile, Johnny has received the deadliest weapon of all time-The Ultimate Nullifier!

title: Tales to Astonish  #79
description: None

title: Daredevil  #16
description: Spider-Man duped into attacking Daredevil! After the Masked Marauder has his goons dress up in Daredevil costumes, New York's wall-crawler falls for a switch n' bait against Matt Murdock! Will Daredevil be able to prove his innocence to a fellow hero?

title: Sgt. Fury  #31
description: Captain Sam Sawyer has knowledge of advanced information, and thus has been captured by Nazi forces. Now, he has to talk. But how long will he be able to keep his mouth shut?

title: Avengers  #29
description: The Avengers are assailed by Power Man, the Swordsman, and a brainwashed Black Widow! But Goliath has problems of his own - will he ever be able to return to his normal size?

After Professor Mendel Stromm is let out of jail, Spider-Man keeps close tabs on his former foe. But what is Stromm's connection to Norman Osborn? And what is the Robot- Master planning in his new-found freedom?

title: Fantastic Four  #51
description: This man...this monster! You can't call yourself a fan of Ben Grimm, the ever-lovin' blue-eyed Thing, if you haven't read this issue. 40 years later and it's still one of the greatest Thing stories ever created.

title: Strange Tales  #145
description: S.H.I.E.L.D. pulls out the big guns by deploying Nick Fury Life Model Decoys, (LMDs). The Druid's eggs begin to hatch and all hope is lost. Will Jasper Sitwell prove the hero of the day? Plus, a descendant of Grigori Rasputin threatens Strange with black magic.

title: Tales to Astonish  #80
description: The Incredible Hulk is sent to a brand new dimension....home to Tyranus!

title: Daredevil  #17
description: The Masked Marauder's plot to pit Spider-Man and Daredevil against each other becomes reality, as Spider-Man crashes into the law office of Nelson and Murdock! But what happens when Spidey has the wrong man pegged as Daredevil? Foggy proves he will stop at nothing to win over Karen's affection, while Daredevil and Spider-Man reach a truce. With the two heroes aligned, will the Masked Marauder be eliminated at long last?

title: Uncanny X-Men  #21
description: In the desert dwells Dominus! The X-Men must defeat an enemy they don't dare attack, but Lucifer's robots aren't returning the favor!

title: Two-Gun Kid  #82
description: None

title: Avengers  #30
description: Goliath sets off to South America to find a cure for Quicksilver and the Scarlet Witch's dwindling powers, while the other Avengers take on the Black Widow and her unit once again. This time, Hawkeye wants to take them down all by himself!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #38
description: There's a bounty on Spider-Man's head and Norman Osborn is behind it! As if struggling with homework wasn't enough, Peter Parker must confront the villains who are seeking his life. Also, a chemically-altered boxer named Joe Smith may be stirring up trouble for Spider-Man.

title: Fantastic Four  #52
description: The First Appearance of The Black Panther, T'Challa, as well as the nation of Wakanda!  On a mission in the remote wilderness of Wakanda, the Fantastic Four encounter one of Marvel's most iconic heroes...and are bested in battle by the Black Panther!  But how are the Inhumans involved in this earthly encounter?

title: Strange Tales  #146
description: Who is 'THEM' and what is A.I.M.? Marvel's resident mad scientists in their first ever appearance! Advanced Idea Mechanics have their eye on the future- but could their vision be a nightmare for the rest of us? Plus, can Eternity be defeated? Dormammu, Lord of the Dark Dimension, seems to think so!

title: Tales of Suspense  #79
description: Tony Stark has returned to the States after his big battle to discover that his factories have been closed, his accounts frozen, and a warrant out for his arrest.

title: Tales to Astonish  #81
description: The Secret Empire has hired Boomerang for a very special job...

title: Daredevil  #18
description: Foggy's bravado reaches a new low as he continues to tell Karen Page that he is Daredevil. After having a Daredevil costume made in his size, Foggy agrees to a mock battle with the costume's designer. Foggy and Karen's date goes horribly awry when the mock battle turns into a fight to the death! Will the real Daredevil step in to save his colleagues? Introducing the Gladiator!

title: Uncanny X-Men  #22
description: The X-Men test their mettle against the robot Colosso, but are lured into a trap by some of Marveldom's earliest super villains! What does Count Nefaria have in mind for them, and for the Maggia?

title: Fantastic Four  #53
description: The First Appearance of Klaw!  Black Panther explains Wakanda's unique history to the FF. Famed for their reservoirs of the rare and near-indestructible metal Vibranium, Wakanda has secluded itself from civilization to protect their precious ores. The origin story of Black Panther, King of Wakanda!

title: Thor  #131
description: Who is Tana Nile? Is she a mysterious, mortal woman...or a creature from beyond? Thor had better gain some answers quickly- especially when Jane Foster's future is at stake!

title: Strange Tales  #147
description: Is A.I.M. as advanced as they claim to be? Nick Fury suspects otherwise after thwarting an attack from some of their goons. Doctor Strange faces a struggle from the earthly realm- getting the Sanctum Sanctorum up to city code!

title: Strange Tales  #147
description: Is A.I.M. as advanced as they claim to be? Nick Fury suspects otherwise after thwarting an attack from some of their goons. Doctor Strange faces a struggle from the earthly realm- getting the Sanctum Sanctorum up to city code!

title: Tales to Astonish  #82
penciler: Gene Colan, Bill Everett, Jack Kirby
description: The Sub-Mariner has come to seek revenge against Iron Man for interfering in his quest to get revenge on Lady Dorma!

title: Uncanny X-Men  #23
description: Framed for extorting Washington, D.C., the X-Men must capitalize on dissension in the Maggia's ranks! Meanwhile, a mysterious figure invades Count Nefaria's command center!

title: Thor  #132
description: The God of Thunder is careening towards the planet Rigel, intent on saving Earth from the usurping Tana Nile. But Thor's mission is soon derailed...by the might of Ego! Introducing one of Marvel's strangest players yet!

title: Daredevil  #20
description: Matt Murdock captured by the Owl! Why is the Owl insisting on a mock trial for Judge Lewis? And will Matt Murdock be able to uphold justice in the face of villainy? Daredevil's secret identity nearly revealed!

title: Uncanny X-Men  #24
description: There are plenty of mad scientists in the Marvel Universe, but few buggier than the Locust! Will his giant insects cut the X-Men down to size?

title: Avengers  #33
description: None

title: Fantastic Four  #55
description: While Reed and Sue make good on their honeymoon, Johnny and Wyatt Wingfoot have a strange encounter with the Silver Surfer! What has brought Galactus' herald to the heights of the Himalayans? Plus, the Thing becomes jealous of Silver Surfer, when he suspects the cosmic being has been making moves on Alicia!

title: Thor  #133
description: Of all the wonders in Asgard, none can compare to the strangeness of...Ego the Living Planet! Will Hulk win over Ego to save Earth from Tana Nile? Meanwhile, Jane Foster gets a teaching offer from a dubious employer.

title: Strange Tales  #149
description: Gabe Jones shows off his impressive undercover work with A.I.M.  Plus, the identity of 'THEM'! Doctor Strange summons the Eye of Agamotto in battle with Kaluu. The NYPD joins the fray when the Sanctum's mystical barriers fall down!

title: Tales of Suspense  #82
description: Tony Stark flies into Washington D.C. to present himself to the hearing in his Iron Man armor, however on the way he is attacked by the newly revived Titanium Man who was launched into Washington D.C. by the Soviets.

title: Daredevil  #21
inker: Dick Ayers, Bill Everett, Frank Giacoia
description: Daredevil continues to battle the Owl in his Owl Airie despite an impending volcanic eruption. With this situation heating up quite literally, will Daredevil be able to escape with his life? The Owl sharpens his beak when he unleashes an owl robot on DD and Judge Lewis!

title: Uncanny X-Men  #25
description: El Tigre seeks the power of a god, and the X-Men are in his way! With Marvel Girl gone from their ranks, do they have a prayer of stopping him?

title: Fantastic Four  #56
description: Ulysses Klaw returns for revenge! Following his defeat in Wakanda at the hands of the FF, Klaw attacks the Baxter Balding armed with sonic super powers! While attempting to escape from the Hidden Land, the Inhumans have an unfortunate accident.

title: Thor  #134
description: Jane Foster, under the employ of the High Evolutionary! Thor discovers the brutish and strange science of the High Evolutionary while trailing Jane in Wundagore. Scarlet Witch and Quicksilver make an appearance!

title: Strange Tales  #150
description: Hydra employs some new methods in taking down S.H.I.E.L.D. HQ. Will Fury walk straight into a trap? Doctor Strange and the Ancient One begin their quest to find the Book of Vishanti. First stop? Ancient Babylonia!

title: Tales of Suspense  #83
description: While battling the Titanium Man in Washington D.C., Iron Man soon finds that Pepper Potts, the girl he loves, is caught in the Titanium Man's paralyzer ray.

title: Fantastic Four Annual  #2
description: A special double-sized issue! Double the action! Double the terror! Doctor Doom has the Fantastic Four right where he wants them. Will the FF be able to stand against their menace? Also featuring the twisted back story of Doctor Doom, the Fantastic Four's cruelest nemesis to date.

title: Tales to Astonish  #85
description: Hulk is being hunted in New York City, which turns into quite a debacle when his rage is worked up. Is being a household name all it's cracked up to be?

title: Fantastic Four Annual  #3
description: The wedding of Sue and Reed! Note: This 24-page digital comic features the original content from this issue, and does not include the reprints of Fantastic Four #6 & #11 that appeared in the 1965 print edition.

title: Fantastic Four Annual  #4
description: Johnny and Wyatt reunited with the Fantastic Four at long last! Lockjaw, teleporting dog to the Inhumans, hurtles through dimensions in this exciting annual issue! Johnny Storm vs. the original Human Torch! The Hulk vs. the Thing! The Fantastic Four's greatest moments collected here!

title: Avengers  #35
description: None

title: Thor  #135
description: The Man-Beast attacks! Thor and the New Men must neutralize the High Evolutionary's most misbegotten experiment. Featuring a surprise ending no True Believer will expect!

title: Daredevil  #23
description: Daredevil takes on the three men morphed into the Tri-Man to secure the Masked Marauder's Maggia membership. That is, assuming the Marauder's men defeat Daredevil! Matt Murdock channels the boxing in his blood to take down Gladiator and Masked Marauder in one fell swoop!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #44
description: Dr. Connors reacts from The Rhino antidote he was previously working on and turns into The Lizard. Realizing this, he runs away but is spotted by his son Billy. The Lizard plots his human conquest and plans to defeat Spider-Man.

title: Fantastic Four  #58
description: After leeching the powers of Silver Surfer, a cosmically-endowed Doctor Doom takes on the FF! A shocking outcome to the team's most significant battle yet! Doom laughs in the face of defeat, and takes on the United States in his latest bid at world domination.

title: Thor  #136
description: Will Jane Foster pass the test of the gods? Odin allows Jane to accept the mantle of a goddess...but only if she can overcome the trials of Asgard. Lady Sif catches Thor's eye.

title: Strange Tales  #152
description: Into the Dimension of Death! Dr. Strange finds himself hurtling through the endless wastes of nowhere, on a fateful journey to the dark dimension beyond the furthest reach of mortal comprehension!

title: Tales of Suspense  #85
description: A tale of dual duels! Tony Stark must save Happy Hogan from the Mandarin - by building a new suit of armor! And Cap locks horns with one of his most persistent foes - Batroc the Leaper!

title: Tales to Astonish  #87
description: The Hulk is so powerful, a villain must be created to destroy him. Thus brings the battle of Hulk vs. Hulk-Killer!

title: Fantastic Four  #59
description: The Inhumans, free at last! Black Bolt shatters the barrier that has trapped the Inhumans in the Hidden Land. In New York, the Fantastic Four must play military strategist and world savior in the global battle against Doom!

title: Thor  #137
description: Ulik's first appearance! When Lady Sif is captured by Geirrodur, King of the Trolls, Thor is lured into battle. But Thor isn't expecting as worthy a combatant as Ulik, the Rock Trolls' most powerful warrior!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #46
description: Peter moves in with Harry and is confronted by The Shocker for the first time!

title: Fantastic Four  #60
description: Doomsday for the Silver Surfer! Robbed of power and imprisoned in Latveria, the Surfer continues to be tortured by Doom's guards.  Will Galactus' herald plot his escape? The Inhumans start to construct their new home following the fall of Attilan!

title: Thor  #138
description: One who is Unworthy steals the hammer of Thor! But will they be able to wield Mjolnir? Plus, behold the mystic might of the Orb of Orikal!

title: Ghost Rider  #2
description: Wrath of the Witch-Woman! The malicious mystic has sentenced Johnny Blaze's soul to damnation, and even his powers as Ghost Rider can't help him! Guest-starring Daimon Hellstrom!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #47
description: Kraven the Hunter hunts...Norman Osborn?  Can Spidey stop one enemy from destroying another?

title: Fantastic Four  #61
description: Sandman's stalking the FF! And when Mister Fantastic falls into the Negative Zone, his teammates fear for the worst!

title: Thor  #139
description: The Asgardian Troll War heats up, as Lady Sif leads Thor to Trollheim to do battle with Ulik and his ilk. Will Orikal be freed at least?

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #48
description: Spider-Man searches the city for a trace of Kraven the Hunter.

title: Fantastic Four  #62
description: Reed Richards stands alone in the Negative Zone! But his isolation is soon broken by the mighty Blastaar! In the Baxter Building, the Inhumans scramble with the FF to recover their missing leader.

title: Thor  #140
description: Will Thor be triumphant over the Growing Man? And which familiar villain spawned this gargantuan foe?

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #49
description: Hearing about the Vulture's defeat of Spider-Man, Kraven becomes furious that he was denied his right to defeat the wall crawler and vows to hunt down his new enemy.

title: Fantastic Four  #63
description: Mister Fantastic has been pulled from the Negative Zone...but so has living bomb Blastaar! Sandman and Blastaar rampage against the FF. Good thing Inhuman friends Crystal and Triton are on hand for battle!

title: Thor  #141
description: Will Chuda's plan for world domination come to fruition? Not if Slugger Sykes has his say! Meanwhile, Thor takes on the mighty Replicus.

title: Thor  #142
description: Loki orchestrates a new plan to destroy Thor by instigating an attack by the deadly Super-Skrull on the God of Thunder!

title: Not Brand Echh  #1
writer: Gary Friedrich, Stan Lee, Roy Thomas
inker: Mike Esposito, Frank Giacoia, John Severin, Marie Severin
description: The first appearance of Forbush Man!  Four spoofy stories in one bust-out-loud-laughing issue! Here, meet the mighty Silver Burper! Then, you’ve read the fateful meeting between original Young Allies Human Torch and the Sub-Mariner, but have you met…The Human Scorch and Sunk-Mariner?!

title: Not Brand Echh  #2
writer: Gary Friedrich, Stan Lee, Roy Thomas
description: Who says a comic book has to be good?? Featuring the stories "Peter Pooper Vs. Gnatman and Rotten", "Magnut, Robot Biter!" and "The Blunder Agents”! This comic is unlike any that you have EVER read before!

title: Thor  #144
description: Odin faces his own challenger, while Thor, Sif and Balder have a scrape with Magnir and Brona. And, Volstagg takes center stage in his own tale of mystery!

title: Fantastic Four Annual  #5
letterer: Sam Rosen, Gaspar Saladino, Art Simek
description: Black Panther and the Inhumans storm the Psycho-Man's base, where they must do battle with...Lockjaw!? But that's not all, as Reed and Sue have a stunning announcement that will change the Fantastic Four forever!

title: Not Brand Echh  #3
writer: Gary Friedrich, Stan Lee, Roy Thomas
penciler: Jack Kirby, John Romita Sr., Artie Simek
inker: Frank Giacoia, Tom Sutton, John Verpoorten
letterer: Sam Rosen, Gaspar Saladino, Art Simek
description: Four more spoofy stories that will tickle your funny bone! Witness the transformation of Dr. Darn Bloke…into the Mighty Sore of Jazzgard! Then, it’s the origin of Brucie Banter and his grouchy, teenage-hating alter ego…the Inedible Bulk! And stay tuned for “The Honest-to-Irving, True-Blue, Top-Secret Original Origin Of Charlie America”! There’s not much super about this soldier!

title: Fantastic Four  #67
description: Deep in Lock 41 of the Beehive, Alicia encounters some of the organization's horrifying experiments. 'Him' emerges from a cocoon, intent on the destruction of its creators. The FF pulls off their most daring rescue mission yet!

title: Thor  #145
description: The Ringmaster has hypnotized Thor into becoming his next, big act...but will the Thunder God go down without a fight? Odin has stripped Thor of his divine powers- and the timing couldn't be worse!

title: Not Brand Echh  #4
writer: Gary Friedrich, Stan Lee, Roy Thomas
description: Featuring: "Defeated by the Evil Electrico"! And meet Splat Murdock…A.K.A. Scaredevil! No, not MATT Murdock. Who the heck is that??

title: Fantastic Four  #68
description: A cure for Ben Grimm? Mister Fantastic collaborates with a renowned doctor to reverse the Thing's mutations. But will the procedure go off without a hitch? Johnny introduces his crew to Crystal!

title: Thor  #146
description: Sif and Balder watch helplessly as a de-powered Thor faces a debacle with the Circus of Crime. Will Odin find the mercy to make his son worthy again?

title: Strange Tales Annual  #2
description: A jealous Human Torch wanted to derail Spidey's day, but now the hothead is helping the Wall-Crawler take down notorious art thief, The Fox!

title: Thor Annual  #1
description: Reprinting Journey Into Mystery Annual (1965) #1, available in MU!

title: Not Brand Echh  #5
penciler: Gene Colan, Jack Kirby, Marie Severin, Tom Sutton
description: Three spoofy stories sure to make you bust in laughter! Here, the first appearance of the ever-hapless Forbush Man! He once was a lowly office worker at Marvel Comics…but through the power of perseverance, he now is a self-made (and not fully realized) super hero!

title: Marvel Super-Heroes  #12
description: Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell) in his very first appearance!

title: Thor Annual  #2
description: Thor participates in the Tournament of Titans in hopes of being declared a hero!

title: Fantastic Four  #70
description: The FF quashed the Mad Thinker...but now they must contend with a brainwashed Thing! Will Reed, Sue and Johnny be able to go full force against one of their own? All this and the Thinker's android!

title: Not Brand Echh  #6
description: In "The Wedding of Spidey-Man, or...With This Ring, I Thee Web!", we wonder, who is the lucky bride?? Similarly, in "The Human Scorch Has To... Meet the Family!", Scorch has a meeting with the in-laws! This should go over well!

title: Marvel Super-Heroes  #13
description: The First Appearance of Carol Danvers, who would assume the mantle of Captain Marvel!  Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell) returns and must face down a Kree threat in The Sentry!

title: Not Brand Echh  #7
description: This fantastic comic is all about origins! And who doesn't love an overload of origin stories?! Including "The Origin of... Stuporman!" I wonder who that could be!

title: Sub-Mariner  #1
description: Continued from Iron Man and Sub-Mariner #1! An amnesiac Sub-Mariner is trapped under tons of ice, but Destiny decides to toy with Atlantis' King further by producing memories he hasn't yet recovered!

title: Not Brand Echh  #8
inker: Tom Sutton, John Tartaglione, John Verpoorten
letterer: Joe Rosen, Gaspar Saladino, Art Simek
description: Forbush Man tries to join the ranks of...the mighty Revengers!

title: Avengers  #53
description: It's the Avengers versus X-Men issue! Cyclops takes on Quicksilver.  Angel has a run-in with Wasp and Black Panther. In hand-to-fist combat who will be triumphant? Super powers or mutant abilities?

title: Thor  #153
description: Someone has stolen the Thunder God's hammer! Mysteries abound, as the mighty Thor must track down the thief of the mightier Mjolnir! Plus, Lady Sif incurs an injury.

title: Captain Marvel  #2
description: The Super Skrull returns to prove himself worthy to the emperor by plotting to kill Captain Marvel in exchange for the emperor's daughter.

title: Daredevil  #41
description: Trapped in his own hell, Daredevil's hope for escape looks bleak. But fear is where DD thrives, and this predicament is no exception! Foggy runs afoul of the wrong super villain. Who is the Exterminator? Karen and Matt talk about Daredevil's final demise.

title: Fantastic Four  #76
description: Journey to Sub-Atomica! Reed, Johnny and Ben travel through the Microverse to bring back the Silver Surfer. The crew finds Silver Surfer, all right...and a heap of particulate problems!

title: Thor  #154
description: Thor nearly has Loki in the palm of defeat, until Odin shows up! What is this new threat against Asgard Odin speaks of? And will the God of Thunder allow Loki to escape his grasp yet again? Guest-starring Karnilla the Norn Queen!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #62
description: Medusa has come to Earth on a goodwill mission on behalf of the Inhumans. But is that's the case, why is she slugging it out with Spidey?

title: Captain Marvel  #3
description: FROM THE ASHES OF DEFEAT! Defeated, Captain Marvel gets even and reveals the Super Skrull's identity and sends him packing back to space.

title: Daredevil  #42
description: A new villain comes out to play, and this one considers himself quite the jokester! Meet Jester, a maniacal thief filled to the brim with gimmicks and gadgets. Matt uses his 'twin brother alter ego' Mike Murdock to take down his most twisted foe yet!

title: Not Brand Echh  #9
inker: Frank Giacoia, Jim Mooney, Sam Rosen, Tom Sutton, John Verpoorten
description: The Puppet Mister has gained complete and utter control of The Inedible Bulk and orders him to attack Prince No-More, the Sunk-Mariner! Totally not a parody of Tales to Astonish #100 or anything like that...promise.

title: Silver Surfer  #1
description: Silver Surfer's origin on Zenn-La revealed here!

title: Fantastic Four  #77
description: Trapped in the Microverse- at the hands of Psycho-Man! The Silver Surfer may have safely returned to Earth, but Reed, Johnny and Ben are still locked in battle against a megalomaniacal foe. Meanwhile, the threat of Galactus looms ever larger.

title: Thor  #155
description: Mangog continues to storm Asgard to as his plot of revenge thickens. Could this be the coming of Ragnarok as Odin predicted? Thor fights against Asgard's End of Days, but the battle may well be out of his hands!

title: The Amazing Spider-Man  #63
description: It's not often that Spider-Man has to break up a fight between two super villains. But this time it's Vulture against Vulture!

title: Captain Marvel  #4
description: Captain Marvel battles his conflicts between being a Kree soldier and his compassion for humanity.

title: Captain America  #105
description: Captain America battles Batroc the Leaper!

title: Fantastic Four  #78
description: Reed Richards succeeds in reverting Ben Grimm back to normal...and now, the Thing is no more! But the timing couldn't be worse- the Wizard launches an attack on the FF, and the team is without its primary muscle! Plus, dangerous complications threaten Sue's pregnancy!

title: Thor  #156
description: Balder finds himself in deep trouble after rejecting the love of Karnilla Queen of Norn. "Hell hath no fury like"...you know the rest. Thor goes into battle with Mangog, the demonic creature intent on bringing Ragnarok to Asgard. When the God of Thunder is joined by the Warriors Three, will the scales of victory at last be tipped in Asgard's favor?

title: Doctor Strange  #172
description: Dormammu has Strange, Clea, and Victoria locked up with no way out!

title: Sub-Mariner  #5
description: Watch out for Tiger Shark in his FIRST ever appearance!

title: Silver Surfer  #2
description: Silver Surfer's naptime is interrupted by a meteor shower...and later -- a Badoon invasion!

title: Fantastic Four  #79
description: Ben Grimm makes the ultimate sacrifice to save the woman he loves. Will Alicia Masters be safe from the Android Man? Sue's pregnancy raises concern for mother and baby.

title: Thor  #157
description: Balder the Brave, Warrior Prince of Asgard, versus the mighty Mangog! Will an entire army of Asgardian soldiers be enough to thwart the coming of Ragnarok? Find out in the explosive conclusion to Mangog's siege of Asgard.

title: Doctor Strange  #173
description: The Sorcerer Supreme is caught in the midst of a mystical sibling rivalry when he's used as a pawn by Umar against her brother Dormammu!

title: Thor  #171
description: After the shooting of civil rights activist Pedro Luis Lopez, Thor springs into action...as Donald Blake! Will Dr. Blake be able to save Lopez's life before the city erupts into race riots? The Destroyer makes a less than triumphant return, leaving Donald Blake/Thor with even more on his plate!
